description: Welcome to 83 Baxter Street, a rare 4-bedroom, detached single-family home in South Boston's vibrant West Side. This newly renovated property offers privacy with no shared walls and abundant space for comfortable living or remote work. The main level features an open floor plan with a spacious living room and gas fireplace, a stunning kitchen with high-end appliances and quartz countertops, and a dining room ideal for entertaining. Step onto the sunny southwest-facing deck, perfect for relaxing or hosting. Upstairs, spread across two levels, are four bedrooms and two beautifully finished full baths. Enjoy the convenience of nearby popular cafes, restaurants and fitness studios like Tatte, Castle Island Brewing, Shybird, Bar Volpe, B/Spoke and F45. The future Old Colony/Dot Ave development will add even more restaurants, retail, and cafes. This meticulously crafted standalone home is a rare opportunity to embrace modern living in one of Boston’s most sought-after neighborhoods.
